        (Aside)<br/><i><br/>Time to back up for a second.<br/><br/>Through some keen observations by Dave, we've established that at the last time the executive assistant's laptop was backed up (ie, last time it was plugged into the corporate LAN), there was a mystery CD in the laptop.  This is the same laptop that was supposedly stolen from her home.  The CD looks interesting, but how do we find the CD?  How do we find out what was on the CD?  Why was the CD made?  Does the whole case revolve around this one CD?<br/><br/>One thing to keep in mind during this case file - the NAME of the case file.  :-)<br/><br/></i><br/>(/Aside)<br/><br/>Our story continues...<br/><br/>Paper as far as the monkey eye could see - scattered all over the table at the local Starbucks.  Dave and I were entrenched doing some background work on the executive assistant,  Mick Thomas, VonHeffer, and multiple binders of company policies and procedures.<br/><br/>Lots of interesting facts were added to our case notes:<br/><br/>* The Executive Assistant (EA) did indeed report the break-in and theft to the police, however no homeowners claim was filed on her possessions.  Not uncommon - a homeowner's claim is a death blow to ever getting homeowner's insurance within three years.  Don't you love how the insurance racket works?<br/><br/>* Interviews with other staff members revealed that the EA and Mick Thomas were known to eat lunch together and socialize on numerous occasions.<br/><br/>* Mick Thomas not only had full access to the company's CVS (source code) servers, but administrator and root access to all other machines.  This was in violation of the company's network security policy, but no violation reports were ever filed.<br/><br/>* A risk analysis was done by the legal department about six months before Mick Thomas left the company.  All five stages of a RA were completed, and one of the largest financial risks mentioned was the theft of intellectual property (the source code) of their product line.<br/><br/>* The company CFO, Izzy Landers, has been on vacation since the theft of the EA's laptop and unreachable by cell phone.<br/><br/>* Izzy and VonHeffer were college roommates.<br/><br/>* Izzy used to work for TouchThemSoft about one year before the EA's laptop was stolen.  No non-compete suit was ever filed by TouchThemSoft over this move.  Interesting.<br/><br/>"You know what I'm thinking?" I said to Dave as I took a swig of a most caffeinated house blend.<br/><br/>"This was a bad week to stop smoking crack?" Dave joked.<br/><br/>"If I was going to burn a CD with a bunch of potentially damaging (and we're assuming damaging) documents on it, what machine would I use at my company?" I asked.<br/><br/>"Hmmm.  Well, for starters you wouldn't want to use your own machine - so let's assume that the EA burnt the CD but she didn't use her laptop." Dave said.<br/><br/>"Yep, ok - now she needs to find another machine with a burner in it - whose machine is she going to use?" I pondered.<br/><br/>"One that she has access to?   But with her login, she could login to any Windows 2000 workstation on that top-floor network." Dave pointed out.<br/><br/>"Yes - but how many machines had a burner installed!" I expounded.<br/><br/>"Well, according to the hardware inventory... only two." Dave replied.  "One belonged to the VP of Graphic Services who used..... a powermac G4.  And the other was in... oh this is nice!!!"<br/><br/>"Uh?" I replied.<br/><br/>Dave lowered the paper and smiled, spouting off "The only other machine with a burner belonged to...<br/><br/>Mick Thomas!!!<br/><br/>Let's hope that the IT department didn't follow it's machine scrubbing procedures on that machine, Chief." <br/><br/>Yes, indeed.<br/><br/><br/>(Aside)<br/><br/>Ok sleuths... what is going on?  <br/><br/>What are your theories so far?<br/><br/>Hint:  Remember <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20130111235049/http://blogs.ittoolbox.com/security/investigator/archives/000195.asp">this case file</a>?<br/><br/>And why the heck was I drinking a house blend instead of an imported bean?<br/><br/>(/Aside)
    </div>    
    <div class="spacer marginleftgutter">
            <hr/>
    <table width="100%" bgcolor="#FFFFCC" cellpadding="9px">
        <tr>
            <td>
                <div style="margin-right: 9px; float: left; height: 60px; width: 60px" lazysource="http://userimages.ittoolbox.com/user/s_610000.jpg"></div>
